data.title: Dortmund's Kehl signs one-year extension
data.meta_description: Borussia Dortmund captain Sebastian Kehl has put pen to paper on a one-year contract extension, the club confirmed on Friday.The 33-year-old center-half will remain at Signal Iduna Park until the summer of 2014
data.text:
Borussia Dortmund captain Sebastian Kehl has put pen to paper on a one-year contract extension, the club confirmed on Friday.

The 33-year-old center-half will remain at Signal Iduna Park until the summer of 2014.

The former Germany international has spent 11 seasons with Dortmund, appearing in 273 Bundesliga matches to go with 23 goals and 31 caps for his country.

"We are pleased that we were able to retain a key player and role model for another year at Borussia Dortmund," said Michael Zorc, Dortmund's sporting director.

"Borussia Dortmund, our club, the supporters and the city of Dortmund have grown to be a home for me," Kehl told the club's official website. "I am delighted to be a part of this fantastic club until 2014."
